  "doc_id": "23994",
  "text": "It is difficult to discover specific reasons for the low median longevity of the restorations replaced; however, operative technique, material quality, and careful handling according to producer instructions may play important roles. [CITATION_1] As mentioned above, the success or failure of restoration, placed and replaced, depends on the following main factors: the dentist's skills, the patient compliance and the restorative material, factors that are closely related. In addition, the oral hygiene of the patient may also play an important role in the development of secondary caries and discoloration.",
